# Handling Alert Prompts in Selenium Python
1️⃣ What is an Alert in Selenium?
An Alert is a popup message box that appears in the browser to:
    1. Show information
    2. Ask for information
    3. Ask the user to enter input

    Example of alerts
    -----------------
    1. Login information
    2. Delete confirmation
    3. Warning messages

Since alerts are outside the webpage DOM , Selenium cannot interact with them directly using normal locators. 

2️⃣ Alert Class in Selenium
Selenium provides an Alert class to handle alerts.
    from selenium.webdriver.common.alert import Alert

This class allows us to : 
    1. Accept alert
    2. Dismiss alert
    3. Get alert text
    4. Send input to alert

3️⃣ Alert Methods
Method & Description
--------------------
1. accept() -> Click OK button
2. dismiss() -> Click Cancel button
3. send_keys() -> Send input to alert textbox
4. text -> Gets alert message

4️⃣ Steps to Handle Alert
1. Open browser
2. Navigate to webpage
3. Trigger the alert
4. Switch to alert
5. Perform action (accept/dismiss/send_keys)

5️⃣ Example 1 – Accepting an Alert
from selenium import WebDriver
from selenium.webdriver.commom.alert import Alert
import time

driver=WebDriver.FireFox()
driver.get("https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/")
time.sleep(10)
alert=Alert(driver)
print(alert.text)
alert.accept()
driver.quit()

    Explanation:
    alert=Alert(driver)  # Switches control to the alert popup.
    alert.text # Retrieves the text message displayed in the alert.
    alert.accept() # Clicks the OK button to accept the alert.

6️⃣ Example 2 – Dismissing an Alert
from selenium import WebDriver
from selenium.webdriver.common.alert import Alert
driver=WebDriver.FireFox()
driver.get("https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/")
alert=Alert(driver)
alert.dismiss()
driver.quit()

    Explanation:
    alert.dismiss() # Clicks the Cancel button to dismiss the alert.

7️⃣ Example 3 – Sending Input to Alert
from selenium import WebDriver
from selenium.webdriver.common.alert import Alert
driver=WebDriver.FireFox()
driver.get("https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/")
alert=Alert(driver)
alert.send_keys("Hello, Geeks!")
alert.accept()
    Explanation:
    alert.send_keys("Hello, Geeks!") # Sends the specified text to the alert's input field.
    alert.accept() # Clicks the OK button to submit the input.

8️⃣ Types of Alerts
    1️⃣ Simple Alert
    Shows message and an OK button.

    Example
    -------
    Are you sure Ok?
    [ OK ]  
Use alert.accept() to click OK.

    2️⃣ Confirmation Alert
    Shows message with OK and Cancel buttons.

    Example
    -------
    Do you want to delete this item?
    [ OK ] [ Cancel ]

    USe alert.accept() to click OK and alert.dismiss() to click Cancel.

    3️⃣ Prompt Alert
    Shows message with input field and OK/Cancel buttons.

    Example
    -------
    Please enter your name:
    [ Input Field ]
    [ OK ] [ Cancel ]   

    Use alert.send_keys() to enter text, alert.accept() to click OK, and alert.dismiss() to click Cancel.

9️⃣ Important Note

Before performing any action on the alert, you must switch to it using Alert(driver). 
Otherwise, Selenium will throw a NoAlertPresentException.